sec.p:
The endothermic sulfuric acid decomposition proceeds at a temperature over 1050 K. There are three sub-steps for the sulfuric acid decomposition:
H2SO4 solution is vaporized to concentrated sulfuric acid;
Concentrated sulfuric acid decomposes into SO3 and H2O;
The unstable SO3 decomposes into SO2 and O2.

